    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Coverings and curtains, usually black in color, placed over sculptures, paintings, mirrors, and other elements at an altar or elsewhere in a church, or in another public or private building; used to signify mourning, such as during a requiem service or during a mourning period. For similar coverings designed particularly for the Lenten season, prefer "Lenten veils." For banners used in procession or hung in funerary settings, use "mourning banners."</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
